def fortune(f0, p, c0, n, i):
    f = f0
    c = c0
    
    for year in range(n-1):
        f = int(f + f * (p/100)) - int(c)
        c = int(c + c * (i/100))
            
    return f >= 0

def fortune(f0, p, c0, n, i):
    
    year = 1
    while f0 > 0 and year < n:
        f0 = f0 * (1 + p / 100) - c0
        f0 = int(f0)
        c0 = c0 * (1 + i / 100)
        c0 = int(c0)
        year += 1
        
    return True if f0 >= 0 else False

def fortune(f0, p, c0, n, i):
    inf = c0
    money = f0
    for j in range(n-1):
        money = int(money + money*(p/100) - inf)
        inf = int(inf + inf*(i/100))

    return True if money >= 0 else False
